The Method Network

The Method Network - Aims

The Method Network - Aims

  • Advance Lukes research by promoting the use of state-of-the-art research methodology

  • Facilitate networking and knowledge maintenance among methodological researchers located in different units and groups

The Method Network - Branches

The Method Network - Branches

Branches of Method Network at Luke:

  • Statistical Methods

  • GIS

  • Bioinformatics

  • Machine learning

  • Scientific Computing

The Method Network - Actions

The Method Network - Actions

  • Training

  • Small-scale consultation

  • Networking & peer-support

  • Participation in maintenance of relevant software and computing infrastructure

Bioinformatics Network at Luke

Bioinformatics Network at Luke

Current state of the Bioinformatics Network at Luke:

  • We started to connect people working in Bioinformatics

  • Teaching has begun:
    • Introduction to Metagenomics
    • Introduction to Snakemake
    • Introduction to RNA-Seq

  • Establishing analysis pipelines

  • Improvement of visibility of the group

  • Network-Meeting scheduled for autumn

Joining the network

Joining the network

  • If you are working in bioinformatics, please feel free to contact me to join the network

  • If you need bioinformatics support, please contact persons directly. If they are overworked, they will redirect you to others

  • Dont be shy, ask! Contact various networks before you spend time and efforts to save time and efforts!

  • If there is demand for education, please feel free to reach out as well

  • Join our (rather silent) Teams channel ( code: r4pjdgk )
